snippet: Jeff Bezos, chief executive of Amazon.com, said in a statement that the spacecraft reached 58 miles high and parachuted to a landing in the West Texas desert.
abstract: Blue Origin, private space company, initiates its first test flight, launching unmanned spacecraft 58 miles over Texas desert; company, founded by Amazon chief executive Jeff Bezos, is hoping to send passengers on suborbital trips.
lead_paragraph: Jeff Bezos, chief executive of Amazon.com, said in a statement that the spacecraft reached 58 miles high and parachuted to a landing in the West Texas desert.

headline.main: Bezos Spaceship Completes Its First Test Flight
